Right to a Maintenance: As may be &s;een by a Paper $word$ $word$
And after this Fa$tion in the Lower Hou&s;e had $word$ Mr. <HI>Mar&s;&s;on,</HI>
&s;on the&s;e Pa&s;&s;ages in his Se$mon, they proceed $word$ $word$ $$|nance
(which is only a Re&s;olution of both Houses to $word$ $word$
of his Sala$$ &s;ettled on him by Act of Parliament, and $word$ be|&s;ide
